You are at:Home»All News Categories»Home Décor»Sona Chawla Named Walgreen’s E-Commerce President 














			Sona Chawla Named Walgreen’s E-Commerce President			



                    By                    Mike Duff

on				
January 17, 2011


Home Décor, Retail, Small Electrics, Web Briefs




Twitter

Facebook

Google+

Pinterest

LinkedIn

Tumblr

Email










Walgreens has promoted Sona Chawla, former senior vp/e-commerce, to president of e-commerce.  Chowla’s promotion was one of several appointments the company has made that suggest it is looking to enhance its strategic decision making capabilities.  The drug chain’s e-commerce offering has become wide ranging and products available include an array of home goods and related gift items, some incorporated into seasonal assortments, that range from hair dryers to juicers to blood-pressure monitors and from clocks to folding tables, even to a GPS navigation system.  “Under Sona’s visionary leadership, we have made extraordinary progress in our online, mobile and e-commerce capabilities,” said Greg Wasson, Walgreen’s president and CEO.
In other executive moves, Walgreens:

Named Graham Atkinson, formerly president of Mileage Plus for United Airlines, as senior vp and chief customer experience officer.
Promoted Mia Scholz, formerly corporate vp/accounting and controller, to senior vp/accounting and controller.
Promoted Robert Zimmerman, formerly vp/corporate development, to senior vp and chief strategy officer.

 













